\ Regression: a string literal inside an anonymous quotation must survive GC.
\ The quotation's CFA and body are emitted inline inside the enclosing word's
\ compiled body, between a (branch) that skips them at run time and a
\ (literal) that publishes the xt. mark_body must walk into the embedded body
\ cell by cell so the (dostr) op marks the template string.
\
\ A previous bug treated the embedded docol cell as a 2-cell call site and
\ skipped the first body cell of the quotation. When that first cell was a
\ (dostr) op, the template went unmarked, got swept, and the next invocation
\ of the quotation dereferenced a NULL Object and segfaulted.

: msg-xt  [: "msg" :] ;

msg-xt execute drop
gc
msg-xt execute drop
gc
.s
